com.squareup.jnagmp

Class LibGmp.mpz_t

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sun.jna.Pointer
      • com.squareup.jnagmp.LibGmp.mpz_t
  • Enclosing class:
    LibGmp

    public static class LibGmp.mpz_t
extends com.sun.jna.Pointer
    Pointer to a native libgmp __mpz_struct; equivalent to mpz_t.

    Must point to an allocated block of memory at least SIZE bytes large. This struct does not manage its own memory, the memory must be managed externally.

    Initialize the structure by calling LibGmp.__gmpz_init(com.squareup.jnagmp.LibGmp.mpz_t) or LibGmp.__gmpz_init2(com.squareup.jnagmp.LibGmp.mpz_t, com.sun.jna.NativeLong), and clean up by calling LibGmp.__gmpz_clear(com.squareup.jnagmp.LibGmp.mpz_t). You MUST clear the structure before the underlying memory is de-allocated, or you will leak native memory.

    We chose not to extend Structure because that would add extra marshaling overhead for no benefit. We don't need direct field access because libgmp manages the struct internals opaquely.

    See Also:
    Initializing Integers
